<paragraph id="7A0AC81D23783A7986E5BABD84379959" blockId="41.[211,1172,1180,1395]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">
Epigyne resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A7987CDBABC87D3989E" authorityName="Moradmand &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2012" box="[507,655,1180,1204]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kronebergi" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A7987CDBABC87D3989E" box="[507,655,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. kronebergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="53F2A97423783A7984A0BABD87A79899" box="[662,763,1180,1203]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having EFB fused to AMLL bordering MS (
<figureCitation id="E28ED49823783A79876ABA9A848298F9" box="[348,478,1211,1235]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Figure 18C</figureCitation>
) but differs from it by presence of a strong continuous ridge at lateral side of vulva and one large glandular process (
<figureCitation id="E28ED49823783A798556BAFA815D98D9" box="[864,1025,1243,1267]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Figure 18D,E</figureCitation>
), in contrast vulva of 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A79870FBADD84939939" authorityName="Moradmand &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2012" box="[313,463,1275,1299]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kronebergi" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79870FBADD84939939" box="[313,463,1275,1299]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. kronebergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="53F2A97423783A7987EEBADD87639939" box="[472,575,1276,1299]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has two small and separated glandular parts; It can also be distinguished by the eye interdistances: AME–ALE spaced one-half of AME– AME (as in 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E23783A79876BBB1D84AB9979" authorityName="Denis" authorityYear="1958" box="[349,503,1339,1363]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscimanus">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79876BBB1D84AB9979" box="[349,503,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">E. fuscimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) but differs from this species in having EF longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="E28ED49823783A7986EDBB7A84039959" box="[219,351,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Figure 18C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32AF9B9623783A7B86E5BB9A87149E54" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="2481" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479" type="description">
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D23783A7986E5BB9A843599F9" blockId="41.[211,361,1467,1491]" box="[211,361,1467,1491]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A7986E5BB9A843599F9" box="[211,361,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Redescription</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D23783A7986E5BBC287579AB0" blockId="41.[211,1171,1506,1690]" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A7986E5BBC2847E99D1" box="[211,290,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">Female</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="48C1140F23783A79870EBBC2841999D0" box="[312,325,1507,1530]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="2479">n</emphasis>
= 3). Total length: 14.9–18.9, prosoma length 6.4–9.1, prosoma width 5.7–7.8, anterior width of prosoma 3.2–4.7, opisthosoma length 8.5–9.8, opisthosoma width 6.5–7.4. eyes are the same size, eye diameters: AME 0.39, ALE 0.41, PME 0.40, PLE 0.40; eye interdistances: AME–AME 0.28, AME–ALE 0.15, PME–PME 0.43, PME–PLE 0.62, AME–PME 0.53, ALE–PLE 0.35, clypeus height at AME 0.32, clypeus height at ALE 0.46.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2ECA9895237B3A7A86B9B809847B9ABF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="2480" startId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" targetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" targetPageId="42">
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237B3A7A86B9B809847B9ABF" blockId="42.[143,1104,1576,1685]" pageId="42" pageNumber="2480">
Figure 18. 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E237B3A7A873FB80887D19A14" authority="Caporiacco, 1935" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[265,653,1576,1598]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="42" pageNumber="2480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237B3A7A873FB808849B9A14" box="[265,455,1577,1598]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="2480">Eusparassus pontii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1E24B5EC237B3A7A87E2B80987D19A14" author="Caporiacco L di" box="[468,653,1576,1598]" pageId="42" pageNumber="2480" pagination="161 - 263" refId="ref23375" refString="Caporiacco L di. 1935. Aracnidi dell'Himalaia e del Karakoram, raccolti dalla Missione italiana al Karakoram (1929 - VII). Mem Soc ent ital. 13: 161 - 263." type="journal article" year="1935">Caporiacco, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86C8BE8686D49D35" blockId="43.[211,1172,167,446]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
Chelicerae with two anterior and four to six posterior teeth; cheliceral furrow without denticles (
<figureCitation id="E28ED498237A3A7B8746BEE684AE9CF5" box="[368,498,199,223]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Figure 18B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula: 21=43. Measurements of palp and legs: Palp 10.6 [3.3, 1.6, 1.9, 3.8], I 34.7 [9.6, 4.3, 8.7, 9.5, 2.6], II 37.7 [10.7, 4.5, 10.1, 9.6, 2.8], III 31.1 [9.5, 3.8, 8.2, 7.3, 2.3], IV 34.6 [10.3, 3.9, 8.8, 9.1, 2.5].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86C8BF0686F19D75" blockId="43.[211,1172,167,446]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86C8BF0684339D15" box="[254,367,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Spination.</emphasis>
Palp 131, 001, 1111, 1013; Legs: Femur I–III 323, IV 321 
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B8235BF0681539D15" bold="true" box="[1027,1039,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">/</emphasis>
322; Patella I–IV 000; Tibia 
<date id="0E0BEEDD237A3A7B87B1BF6984A79D75" box="[391,507,327,351]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" value="2024-01" valueMax="2024-04-31" valueMin="2024-01-00">I–IV 2024</date>
; Metatarsus 
<date id="0E0BEEDD237A3A7B84BDBF69865C9D75" box="[651,768,327,351]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" value="2024-01" valueMax="2024-03-31" valueMin="2024-01-00">I–III 2024</date>
, IV 3034 
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B8552BF66862C9D75" bold="true" box="[868,880,327,351]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">/</emphasis>
3036.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86C8BF4986209D94" blockId="43.[211,1172,167,446]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86C8BF4984F89D55" box="[254,420,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
Epigyne 
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B8761BF46843F9D55" bold="true" box="[343,355,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">/</emphasis>
vulva.
</emphasis>
As in diagnosis with two large black triangular LL, AMLL not fused but bordered by EFB (
<figureCitation id="E28ED498237A3A7B842FBFA787C09DB4" box="[537,668,390,414]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Figure 18C</figureCitation>
); vulva with a bulge at the area of glandular processes and marked by a continuous ridge (
<figureCitation id="E28ED498237A3A7B84E6BF8786339D94" box="[720,879,422,446]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="42.[143,210,1576,1598]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-6@42.[145,1102,161,1543]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 18. Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, (A–D) syntype female from Karakoram, Pakistan: (A) eye arrangement; (B) left chelicera, ventral; (C) epigyne, ventral; (D) left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral; (E) variation of left vulva, anterio-dorso-lateral. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm, (D, E) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5202107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5202107/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Figure 18D,E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BFC784C99DD4" blockId="43.[211,405,486,510]" box="[211,405,486,510]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86E5BFC784489DD4" box="[211,276,486,510]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BC0787149E54" blockId="43.[211,1172,550,638]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86E5BC07840A9E14" box="[211,342,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Colouration</emphasis>
[in ethanol]. Reddish brown, dark brown chelicera, dorsal opisthosoma with a patch and series of small chevron-like patterns and additional dots, ventral opisthosoma with pale markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32AF9B96237A3A7B86E5BCE286E19FA8" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BCE284699EF1" blockId="43.[211,309,707,731]" box="[211,309,707,731]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86E5BCE284699EF1" box="[211,309,707,731]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BCCB86E19FA8" blockId="43.[211,1172,746,899]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
The type specimens were collected during “the Italian Mission to Karakoram (
<date id="0E0BEEDD237A3A7B8262BCCB845C9F08" bridgedPair="-" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" value="1929-07">1929- VII</date>
)”. One of the 
<typeStatus id="A50E76BF237A3A7B8782BD2A84B89F09" box="[436,484,779,803]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">type</typeStatus>
localities is Pajue, a campsite on the K2 Mountain. The species is recorded from high elevations (∼ 
<quantity id="BD4D65F8237A3A7B8488BD0B86489F68" box="[702,788,810,834]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" unit="m" value="4000.0">4000 m</quantity>
), the highest altitude recorded for 
<taxonomicName id="BDB5B39E237A3A7B86E5BD6B84049F48" authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1872" box="[211,344,842,866]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sparassidae</taxonomicName>
so far. This is the first record of the species after its original description out of the 
<typeStatus id="A50E76BF237A3A7B877EBD4A84249FA9" box="[328,376,875,899]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">type</typeStatus>
locality, namely from Indian Himalaya, in Ladakh.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32AF9B96237A3A7B86E5BDE98745980D" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BDE987E59FF5" blockId="43.[211,697,967,991]" box="[211,697,967,991]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
<emphasis id="48C1140F237A3A7B86E5BDE987E59FF5" box="[211,697,967,991]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Known geographical distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A0AC81D237A3A7B86E5BDCE8745980D" blockId="43.[211,1172,1007,1063]" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">
High altitudes in mountainous Himalaya in 
<collectingCountry id="02A2888D237A3A7B84F6BDCE867A982D" box="[704,806,1007,1031]" name="Pakistan" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
: Karakoram, K2 Mountain, and 
<collectingCountry id="02A2888D237A3A7B86E5BA2E844F980D" box="[211,275,1039,1063]" name="India" pageId="43" pageNumber="2481">India</collectingCountry>
: Ladakh (New record).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
